<br>
Finally fed up with EQ so I'm gonna give AO a shot again (played first 2 weeks after release).  Have decided on MA as they seem to be able to either solo or group fairly well (not that interested in PvP until I get rid of my newbie-ness), but I still have some questions regarding skills that I can't seem to find an answer to in the newbie guides.<br>
<br>
1) Adventuring - is this used for anything other than to wear backpacks in your back slot?  Are there ANY pros to putting IP here?<br>
<br>
2) Parry - does parry work with a fist-MA or do you need to be using a weapon for it to trigger?  if it does work with fists, is it useful to put IP in?<br>
<br>
3) Fast Attack/Sneak Attack - gonna go with fists until I figure out which 1 weapon skill I want to use (if any).  Are either of these attacks useful for a fist-MA, not just low levels but 100+ as well.<br>
<br>
I pretty much want to save as much IP as possible - I'd hate to get to 50+ and recreate - so any good advice is appreciated as I know jack about AO. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/usotla.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sotla</A> at: 3/8/02 12:29:11 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=publius>Publius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>They call me Bruce.</span><br>  Posts: 397<br> <font color=#660000>(3/8/02 1:02:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1774.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unanswered questions</span><hr size=1> 1a)  Nominally, a higher Adv skill makes you take less damage from falling, yawn<br>
<br>
1b)  No<br>
<br>
2) Good questions, which will no doubt be hotly debated. I leave that debate to others <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
3) Fast Attack <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> may</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be useful for Flurry of Blows. Then again, with all the current confusion over which init skill is really used for what, who knows?<br>
<br>
