<br>
Pub coverd it pretty well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
--2) Parry - does parry work with a fist-MA or do you need to be using a weapon for it to trigger? if it does work with fists, is it useful to put IP in?--<br>
<br>
Parry works reguardless of weapons.  It's a skill check, but like many skills you really have to practice ruthless max'ing and min'ing in AO, the real benefit of parry is use of the Blessed with Thunder attack, arguably the best Martial Arts special attack in game ( hands down best for damage over time, but there are better choices for short term damage ).  Parry ONLY works vs melee attacks ( can't parry bullets ).<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
--3) Fast Attack/Sneak Attack - gonna go with fists until I figure out which 1 weapon skill I want to use (if any). Are either of these attacks useful for a fist-MA, not just low levels but 100+ as well.--<br>
<br>
No, neither of these is used with the MA fist.  I don't recommend putting points in either, eventually you'll have a defualt value for Fast Attack that's high enough to use very low ql Flurry of Blows, so get a low level one and hang onto it.<br>
<br>
--I pretty much want to save as much IP as possible - I'd hate to get to 50+ and recreate - so any good advice is appreciated as I know jack about AO.--<br>
<br>
Okay, works of advice, don't prosue the AC programs for long, the have great value, but dimishing returns on the ip you sink in.  Mat Met is another skill you can for the most part ignore, get enough for the general programs, then stop spending points in it.<br>
<br>
Do NOT however skimp on treatment, it's a hugely important skill.  Max it ever leve and you'll be a lot happier when the time to implant comes.<br>
<br>
