<br>
1) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Adventuring</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:  Adventuring is worthless.  Don't waste any IP there, IMHO.<br>
<br>
2) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Parry</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:  Aidyl (my MA) does not use a weapon and currently has over 300 parry, since it is the primary req for Blessed with Thunder, the Holy Grail of currently viable MA special attacks (until you are high enough to get Shen).  I always play in 3rd person view, and I think I've seen her parry an incoming attack maybe *3* times in her life.  However, mobs parry my attacks like crazy.  I can't tell you how FUN it is to have your DIMACH parried when you are close to death and pulling out all the stops.  &quot;OK, Mr. Red Mob, my heals can't keep up with your damage, and my BwT hasn't recycled yet...here comes my soul attack!  &lt;&quot;Parry!&quot; floats above the head of the mob&gt;  WTF?!?  &lt;Your items will be made available in 60 seconds...&gt;&quot;<br>
<br>
Parry seems to be entirely fubar like Nano Resist (great if you fight grays or greens, useless otherwise). *shrug*<br>
<br>
But it is DEFINITELY worth raising once you hit about 30th and can start using BwT.  I think I had a Q60ish BwT equipped at 32nd level, thanks to some aggressive parry implants.<br>
<br>
3) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Fast Att/Sneak Att</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:  Aidyl doesn't use weapons, but my 40th Atrox MP went 1HB for the eventual MP shields, so he has high Fast Attack and Sneak Attack as reqs for his duel wielding alloy staff/pipe.  Fast Attack is a nice special attack, and does decent dmg, although the FA timer occasionally gets fubared and I'll often have to wait 3-4 fights until it gets &quot;unstuck&quot; (the &quot;Wait for your previous attack to complete&quot; BS.  AO timers are all f*cked up thanks to sloppy coding by FunCom and their bandaid efforts to work around exploits...).  Sneak Attack is pretty much useless unless you also have high concealment, and according to my 50th agent, concealment in general is kinda f'ed up, too.  My agent sometimes goes into backyard training areas as FP: Trader to ransack/deprive poor little leets to equip better rifles, and sometimes with my 600+ conceal, those darn leets STILL spot me and I can't get off my aimed shot to test my newly equipped rifle.  They truly are 1337! *shrug*<br>
<br>
- Rookie Aidyl<br>
